title: Bug 4121: JarExporter causing out of sync message
description: The JarExporter is causing an out of sync message when overwriting the exported jarfile for a project.
OB: If you export a directory (project) and place the exported jar in the same directory (project), you will receive an out of sync message when you try to overwrite the exported jarfile for the second time.
EB: The JarExporter should not cause an out of sync message when overwriting the exported jarfile for a project.
SR:
1. Open the project directory.
2. Export the directory as a jar file.
3. Place the exported jar file in the same project directory.
4. Attempt to overwrite the exported jar file for a second time.
5. Observe the out of sync message.
